abstract: With more than 2 dozen albums and more than 50 No. 1 hits worldwide, he was a pop superstar, singing about love and heartache.
snippet: With more than 2 dozen albums and more than 50 No. 1 hits worldwide, he was a pop superstar, singing about love and heartache.
lead_paragraph: Camilo Sesto, a Spanish songwriter, singer and producer whose romantic songs have sold more than 180 million copies worldwide, died on Sunday in Madrid. He was 72 and lived in Madrid.

abstract: Mr. Steyer has made the cut for the Democratic presidential debates in October, though he will not be onstage this week. Tulsi Gabbard is also close to securing a spot.
snippet: Mr. Steyer has made the cut for the Democratic presidential debates in October, though he will not be onstage this week. Tulsi Gabbard is also close to securing a spot.
lead_paragraph: Tom Steyer, the billionaire and former hedge fund investor turned impeachment activist, became the 11th Democratic presidential candidate to qualify for the October debates on Sunday after a new poll showed him with 2 percent support in Nevada.

lead_paragraph: Pamela Jane Hinchman and Ted DeDee met in October 2015 at the Overture Center for the Arts in Madison, Wis., where Mr. DeDee had been the president and chief executive. Ms. Hinchman had traveled from Chicago to see a student perform there and was pleasantly surprised when a friend introduced her to Mr. DeDee.

abstract: A Nobel-winning economist goes to Burning Man. Linda Hamilton is back. Margaret Atwood is, too. And “Friends” is turning 25.
snippet: A Nobel-winning economist goes to Burning Man. Linda Hamilton is back. Margaret Atwood is, too. And “Friends” is turning 25.
lead_paragraph: With the first week of September in the books, and the exhale of fall ahead of us, take a moment to catch up on some of our great journalism.

headline_main: Fall Movies 2019: Here’s What’s Coming Soon to Theaters

abstract: The entrepreneur turned presidential candidate is explaining automation to the masses. And as voters realize he is serious and substantive, he is gaining a passionate following.
snippet: The entrepreneur turned presidential candidate is explaining automation to the masses. And as voters realize he is serious and substantive, he is gaining a passionate following.
lead_paragraph: PLAISTOW, N.H. — Meet Andrew Yang supporters and they often have a confession to make: When they first heard about Mr. Yang, they thought his plan to give every American adult $1,000 a month was a little crazy. But then, they will inevitably tell you, they heard him explain it, and it all started making sense.

abstract: At Rutgers Presbyterian Church in Manhattan, social justice and environmental issues unite the congregation. There’s Bible stuff, too.
snippet: At Rutgers Presbyterian Church in Manhattan, social justice and environmental issues unite the congregation. There’s Bible stuff, too.
lead_paragraph: Observant Presbyterians are always part of gatherings at Rutgers Presbyterian Church. But much of the time, so are Roman Catholics and Jews, as well as a smattering of people who consider themselves vaguely spiritual. Valerie Oltarsh-McCarthy, who sat among the congregation listening to a Sunday sermon on the perils of genetically modified vegetables, is, in fact, an atheist.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates recently spoke of the need to address the adverse effects of global warming on poor and marginalized communities.
lead_paragraph: The presidential candidates at the CNN climate forum on Wednesday repeatedly emphasized how climate change is hurting low-income communities and people of color, reflecting a growing awareness among Democrats that many of the problems they seek to address are inextricably tied to racism, poverty and other forms of discrimination and inequality.

abstract: Saying he was “torn between family loyalty and the national interest,” Boris Johnson’s younger brother resigned his ministerial post and his seat in Parliament.
snippet: Saying he was “torn between family loyalty and the national interest,” Boris Johnson’s younger brother resigned his ministerial post and his seat in Parliament.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — They have the same shock of blindingly blond and slightly disheveled hair. They grew up in the same hypercompetitive, overachieving family that held dinner table debates where cleverness was the coin of the realm. They were on opposite sides of the 2016 Brexit referendum but patched things up afterward, as the right sort of people do.
